Package com.thalesgroup.secutils.certpinner

Class CertificatePinner

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.thalesgroup.secutils.certpinner.CertificatePinner
  • public class CertificatePinner
extends Object

    This class currently allows the caller to set the hostname and corresponding pins. The hostname can be mentioned in 3 ways 1) **.thalescloud.io ( matches all subdomains. ex: abc.xyz.thalescloud.io, qrs.thalescloud.io ) 2) *.thalescloud.io ( matches exactly 1 subdomain ex: abc.thalescloud.io, xyz.thalescloud.io ) 3) dev-tls.thalescloud.io ( matches the domain exactly ex: only dev-tls.thalescloud.io can be matched)

    Setting up Certificate Pinning

    The easiest way to pin a host is turn on pinning with a broken configuration and read the expected configuration when the connection fails. Remove the custom trustmanager when calling sslcontext.init to get the pins of each certificate in the chain

    For example, to pin https://publicobject.com, start with a broken configuration: 

       

     String hostname = "publicobject.com";
     CertificatePinner certificatePinner = new CertificatePinner.Builder()
         .add(hostname, new byte[]{0x12,0x45,....})
         .build();
     After httpurlconnection.connect(),
     call certificatePinner.check(hostname,httpurlconnection.getServerCertificates())

     final URL url = new URL("https://dev.thalescloud.io/xx");
     httpURLConnection = (HttpsURLConnection) url.openConnection();

     sslContext = SSLContext.getInstance("TLS");
     final TrustManager[] trustManagers = new TrustManager[] { new X509PinningTrustManager(certificatePinner) };
     sslContext.init(null, trustManagers, null);
     httpURLConnection.setSSLSocketFactory(sslContext.getSocketFactory());
     httpURLConnection.setRequestMethod("GET");
     httpURLConnection.setDoOutput(true);
     httpURLConnection.connect();

    As expected, this fails with a certificate pinning exception:

    Follow up by pasting the public key hashes from the exception into the certificate pinner's configuration Usage: 

       

     final URL url = new URL("https://dev.thalescloud.io/xx");
     httpURLConnection = (HttpsURLConnection) url.openConnection();

     sslContext = SSLContext.getInstance("TLS");
     final TrustManager[] trustManagers = new TrustManager[] { new X509PinningTrustManager(certificatePinner) };
     sslContext.init(null, trustManagers, null);
     httpURLConnection.setSSLSocketFactory(sslContext.getSocketFactory());
     httpURLConnection.setRequestMethod(method);
     httpURLConnection.setDoOutput(true);
     httpURLConnection.connect();

        Utility method to get the pins associated with a hostname after httpsurlconnection.connect()

        Optionally can be used as an additional check to that of X509PinningTrustManger. A small mitigation if pinning is bypassed by readymade scripts

        Throws:
        CertificateException - with detailed pin information for each certificates in debug mode
